HOUSE BILL 1024
M4, M2 5lr3449
CF SB 958
By: Delegates Hutchinson, Adams, Arentz, Beauchamp, Jacobs, and Otto
Introduced and read first time: February 3, 2025
Assigned to: Environment and Transportation
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Agriculture – Catastrophic Damage Caused by Deer
3 FOR the purpose of authorizing the Department of Agriculture to take extraordinary
4 measures to control deer populations and prevent future crop loss under certain
5 circumstances; and generally relating to deer and crop damage.
6 BY adding to
7 Article – Agriculture
8 Section 2–108
9 Annotated Code of Maryland
10 (2016 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
11 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
12 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
13 Article – Agriculture
14 2–108.
15 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “CATASTROPHIC DAMAGE” MEANS THE LOSS OF 50%
16 OR MORE OF CROPS FROM A SINGLE FIELD.
17 (B) IF THE DEPARTMENT DETERMINES THAT DEER HAVE CAUSED
18 CATASTROPHIC DAMAGE TO A FIELD, THE DEPARTMENT MAY TAKE
19 EXTRAORDINARY MEASURES TO CONTROL THE LOCAL DEER POPULATION AND
20 PREVENT FUTURE CROP LOSS.
21 (C) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ADOPT REGULATIONS TO IMPLEMENT THIS
22 SECTION.
